    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "siege_weapon",
        "text": "Trapdoor actuators are designed to be well hidden (usually as part of a cliff face) and operated by small, untrained crews. Cleverly designed springs launch an iron rod from the protective wall. Typically, this level of camouflage allows the trapdoor actuator to remain unnoticed unless a creature succeeds at a DC 18 Perception check to spot it. After a launch, the trapdoor actuator\u2019s camouflage can be reset as a two-action activity.",
        "level": 3,
